CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 13, 1953, pg. 28, reads: "'Miss YWCA' Crowned - Centre Avenue YWCA Residence Girls voted the two young ladies shown above as 'Miss YWCA' and 'Miss YWCA Alternate' for making the greatest contribution to their week-end project, a dance, last week. Miss Earlene Allen, the runner-up, is shown as she crowned Miss Catherine Hobson from Mount Pleasant, Pa. as 'Miss YWCA.'  Another event was the choice of Miss Alice Sluby as delegate to the YWCA Conference for Employed Girls at Lake Sebago, N. Y. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Earlene Allen wearing cross hatch patterned dress placing foil crown on "Miss YWCA" Catherine Hobson
